quest_title: If a, b, c are three non-coplanar vectors such that \(a+b+c=\alpha \, d\) and \(b+c+d=\beta \, a,\) then \(a+b+c+d\) is equal to
explanation_txt:
We have \(a+b+c=\alpha {\rm \; }d\) and \(b+c+d=\beta \, a\)

\({\mkern1mu\raise1pt\hbox{.}\mkern1mu\raise4pt\hbox{.}\mkern1mu\raise1pt\hbox{.}\mkern1mu} \, \, \, a+b+c+d=(\alpha +1)d\) and \(a+b+c+d=(\beta +1)\, a.\)

\[\Rightarrow (\alpha +1)\, d=(\beta +1)\, a\]

If \(\alpha \, \ne \, -1,\) then \((\alpha +1)\, d=(\beta +1)\, a\Rightarrow d=\cfrac{\beta +1}{\alpha +1} a\)

\[ a+b+c=\alpha \, d \Rightarrow a+b+c=\alpha \left(\cfrac{\beta +1}{\alpha +1} \right)a\]

\[\Rightarrow \left(1-\cfrac{\alpha (\beta +1)}{\alpha +1} \right)\, a+b+c=0\]

\(\Rightarrow a,\, b,\, c\) are coplanar which is contradiction to the given condition,

So, \( \alpha = -1 \) and \( a+ b + c + d = 0 \)

explanation_txt:
The curve is equivalent to:

\( y = 1 - x^2 \\ y = x^2-1 \)

For intersection;

\( 1 - x^2 = x^2 - 1 \\ \Rightarrow 2(x^2 - 1) = 0 \\ \Rightarrow x = \pm 1 \)

So, the area is:

\[ A = 2 \left| \int_{-1}^{-1} (x^2 -1) dx \right| = 2 \left | \cfrac{x^3}{3} - x \right|_{-1}^{1} = 4 \times \left| - \cfrac{2}{3} \right| = \cfrac{8}{3} \]

quest_title: The equation of motion of projectile is \(y=12 x-\cfrac{3}{4} x^{2}\). The horizontal component of velocity is 3m/s then range of projectile is
explanation_txt:
\(y=12 x-\cfrac{3}{4} x^{2} \)

\(V_{y}=\cfrac{d y}{d t}=12 \cfrac{d x}{d t}-\cfrac{3}{4} \cdot 2 \mathrm{x} \cfrac{d x}{d t} \)

Initially \(x=0\) so

\(V_{y}=12 \cdot V_{x}=12 \times 3=36 \mathrm{m} / \mathrm{s}\)

\(\tan \theta=\cfrac{V_{y}}{V_{x}} \)
\(\tan \theta=\cfrac{36}{3}=12 \)

\(u \cos \theta=3 \mathrm{m} / \mathrm{s}, u \sin \theta=36 \mathrm{m} / \mathrm{s} \)
\(R=\cfrac{u^{2} \sin 2 \theta}{g}=\cfrac{2(u \sin \theta) \cdot(u \cos \theta)}{g} \)
\(R=\cfrac{u^{2} \sin 2 \theta}{g}=\cfrac{2 \times 36 \times 3}{10}=21.6 \mathrm{m} \)

quest_title: One molar solution of \(\text{KMnO\({}_{4}\)}\) is acidic medium is equivalent to
explanation_txt:
In acidic solution, MnO\({}_{4}\)\({}^{-}\)+8H\({}^{+}\) + 5e\({}^{-}\) \(\rightarrow\) Mn\({}^{++}\) + 4H\({}_{2}\)O

i.e. 2KMnO\({}_{4}\)\({}^{-}\)+16HCl \(\rightarrow\) 2KCl + 2MnCl\(_2\) + 8H\({}_{2}\)O + 5Cl\(_2\)

Change in Oxidation number of Mn = 7-2 = 5

\(\therefore\) Equivalent Weight of KMnO\(_4\) = Molecular weight/Change in oxidation number = M/5

\(\therefore\) 1M of KMnO\(_4\) solution = 5N

explanation_txt:
To develop a print, a fix amount of energy is required.

Total light energy incident on photo print

\(I\times A\, t=\cfrac{L}{r^{2} } A\, t\)

\(\Rightarrow \cfrac{L_{1} }{r_{1}^{2} } A_{1} t_{1} =\cfrac{L_{2} }{r_{2}^{2} } A_{2} t_{2} \)

\(\Rightarrow \cfrac{t_{1} }{r_{1}^{2} } =\cfrac{t_{2} }{r_{2}^{2} } \) (\(\because \; L_{1} =L_{2} \) and \(A_{1} =A_{2} \))

\(\Rightarrow t_{2} =\cfrac{r_{2}^{2} }{r_{1}^{2} }\times t_{1} \)\(=\left(\cfrac{0.40}{0.25} \right)\; 2\times 5= 12.8 \textit{sec}\)
